description:
&lt;p&gt;The Pharmacy department of the Royal Free London NHS Trust is a friendly, progressive and expanding unit dedicated to providing the highest standards of pharmaceutical care and service in this large, internationally renowned teaching hospital. The Trust has good transport links to major mainline train stations such as Kings Cross, Euston, Stratford, London Bridge and Charing Cross.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is an exciting time to come and work in the Pharmacy Production unit at the Royal Free Hospital. We have recently completed a major refurbishment for our non-sterile and CIVAS suites and now have ambitious plans to grow our team and department. We are looking for a Business Development Manager to join the team help develop and expand the commercial division of the unit.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is an exciting opportunity to develop your general skills within business management, leadership and technical services to deliver positive change in a GMP environment. If you fancy the challenge of an environment that is pushing the boundaries of patient care then please consider us for your next career move. The successful candidate is required to be able to demonstrate the trust values, the responsibilities of the job description, person specification and have a strong business and technical services background.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you believe you meet the criteria of the person specification and would like to join the Royal Free at this time, we would be interested in receiving your application. To find out more about working at the Royal Free please visit our website.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name: Rahul Sheth&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title: Deputy Production Manager&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address: Rahul.Sheth@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number: 0207 830 2282 ext 33112&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Additional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Avaliable Mon- Fri (9- 5pm) for site visits.&lt;/p&gt;
